    <main class="main-panel">
      <div class="page-header-area">
        <h1 class="page-title">Accessibility</h1>
        <p class="page-desc">Design accessible endpoint management experiences that work for every IT admin, operator, and analyst.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="main-content-area">
        <div class="main-content-inner">

          <!-- Intro -->
          <div class="doc-section" style="margin-top: 16px;">
            <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--prism-text-muted); max-width: 760px;">Accessibility in Prism ensures that endpoint workflows remain usable across diverse abilities, environments, devices, and situational limitations — whether users are working in SOC environments, on low-vision displays, or managing systems under pressure.</p>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider" />

          <!-- Building accessible endpoint experiences -->
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="building-accessible" class="doc-section-title">Building accessible endpoint experiences</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">An accessible endpoint platform allows users of all abilities to monitor, manage, secure, and remediate devices confidently.</p>
            <p style="font-size: 15px; color: var(--prism-text-muted); margin-bottom: 20px;">Prism components include built-in accessibility support such as:</p>
            <ul class="doc-list">
              <li>Full keyboard navigation</li>
              <li>Logical focus management</li>
              <li>Accessible labels and descriptions</li>
              <li>Screen reader-friendly status messaging</li>
              <li>Semantic component structures</li>
              <li>Motion-safe transitions</li>
              <li>High-contrast token compatibility</li>
            </ul>
            <div style="margin-top: 24px; padding: 16px 20px; background: rgba(37,99,235,0.04); border: 1px solid rgba(37,99,235,0.12); border-radius: 12px; display: flex; gap: 12px; align-items: center;">
              <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--prism-violet)" stroke-width="2" style="flex-shrink: 0;"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M12 16v-4"/><path d="M12 8h.01"/></svg>
              <p style="font-size: 14px; color: var(--prism-text); line-height: 1.6; margin: 0;">Accessibility does not stop at components. Product teams must ensure workflows, dashboards, tables, automation builders, and remediation flows are accessible end-to-end.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider" />

          <!-- Accessibility Principles -->
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="principles" class="doc-section-title">Accessibility principles</h2>
          </div>

          <!-- Principle 1 -->
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h3 id="predictable-workflows" class="doc-h3"><span style="color: var(--prism-violet); font-weight: 700; margin-right: 4px;">1.</span> Build predictable workflows</h3>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Endpoint actions are often high-risk. Users must always know what happens next.</p>
            <h4 style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; color: var(--prism-text-muted); margin-bottom: 12px;">Guidelines</h4>
            <ul class="doc-list">
              <li>Use consistent placement for device actions, filters, search, and bulk operations</li>
              <li>Keep patch deployment, policy assignment, and remediation flows structurally similar</li>
              <li>Reuse interaction patterns across inventory, patch, software, and compliance modules</li>
              <li>Preserve keyboard behavior across all tables and side panels</li>
              <li>Avoid changing control positions between pages</li>
            </ul>
            <div style="margin-top: 20px; padding: 16px 20px; background: rgba(34,197,94,0.05); border: 1px solid rgba(34,197,94,0.2); border-radius: 12px;">
              <p style="font-size: 14px; color: var(--prism-text); line-height: 1.6; margin: 0;"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> Predictability reduces cognitive load and prevents operational mistakes.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider" />

          <!-- Principle 2 -->
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h3 id="reduce-cognitive-overload" class="doc-h3"><span style="color: var(--prism-violet); font-weight: 700; margin-right: 4px;">2.</span> Reduce cognitive overload</h3>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Endpoint platforms naturally contain large data sets, alerts, and actions.</p>
            <h4 style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; color: var(--prism-text-muted); margin-bottom: 12px;">Guidelines</h4>
            <ul class="doc-list">
              <li>Prioritize critical signals over secondary metadata</li>
              <li>Use progressive disclosure for advanced controls</li>
              <li>Break remediation workflows into clear steps</li>
              <li>Avoid dense modal stacking</li>
              <li>Use concise system language</li>
              <li>Keep reading level simple and operational</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="do-dont-grid" style="margin-top: 24px;">
              <div class="do-card"><span class="card-label">Do</span>
                <ul><li>"5 devices failed patch installation"</li><li>"Restart required on 12 endpoints"</li></ul>
              </div>
              <div class="dont-card"><span class="card-label">Avoid</span>
                <ul><li>Overly technical internal engineering phrasing</li><li>Long alert paragraphs</li><li>Multiple warning banners competing for attention</li></ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider" />

          <!-- Principle 3 -->
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h3 id="color-independent-status" class="doc-h3"><span style="color: var(--prism-violet); font-weight: 700; margin-right: 4px;">3.</span> Design for color-independent status</h3>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Security and device health systems often overuse color.</p>
            <h4 style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; color: var(--prism-text-muted); margin-bottom: 12px;">Guidelines</h4>
            <ul class="doc-list">
              <li>Never rely on red, green, or yellow alone</li>
              <li>Pair status colors with icons, labels, and severity text</li>
              <li>Include readable badge labels: <strong>Critical</strong>, <strong>Warning</strong>, <strong>Healthy</strong>, <strong>Pending reboot</strong></li>
              <li>Use patterns or borders for charts and heatmaps</li>
              <li>Ensure dark-mode contrast remains accessible</li>
            </ul>
            <div style="margin-top: 24px; padding: 20px 24px; background: var(--prism-surface); border: 1px solid var(--prism-border); border-radius: 12px;">
              <h4 style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--prism-text); margin-bottom: 12px;">Contrast requirements</h4>
              <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 12px;">
                <div style="padding: 16px; border-radius: 10px; background: rgba(37,99,235,0.04); border: 1px solid rgba(37,99,235,0.1); text-align: center;">
                  <div style="font-size: 24px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--prism-violet);">4.5:1</div>
                  <div style="font-size: 12px; color: var(--prism-text-muted); margin-top: 4px;">Normal text</div>
                </div>
                <div style="padding: 16px; border-radius: 10px; background: rgba(37,99,235,0.04); border: 1px solid rgba(37,99,235,0.1); text-align: center;">
                  <div style="font-size: 24px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--prism-violet);">3:1</div>
                  <div style="font-size: 12px; color: var(--prism-text-muted); margin-top: 4px;">Large text / UI graphics</div>
                </div>
                <div style="padding: 16px; border-radius: 10px; background: rgba(37,99,235,0.04); border: 1px solid rgba(37,99,235,0.1); text-align: center;">
                  <div style="font-size: 24px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--prism-violet);">4.5:1</div>
                  <div style="font-size: 12px; color: var(--prism-text-muted); margin-top: 4px;">Critical action buttons</div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider" />

          <!-- Principle 4 -->
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h3 id="keyboard-first" class="doc-h3"><span style="color: var(--prism-violet); font-weight: 700; margin-right: 4px;">4.</span> Ensure keyboard-first operations</h3>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">IT admins frequently work faster with keyboards.</p>
            <h4 style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; color: var(--prism-text-muted); margin-bottom: 12px;">Guidelines</h4>
            <ul class="doc-list">
              <li>Every action must be reachable without a mouse</li>
              <li>Support keyboard traversal in: <strong>Device tables</strong>, <strong>Tree navigation</strong>, <strong>Alert queues</strong>, <strong>Bulk action drawers</strong>, <strong>Deployment workflows</strong></li>
              <li>Maintain visible focus states</li>
              <li>Use skip links for repetitive dashboard regions</li>
              <li>Enable shortcut discoverability</li>
            </ul>
            <div style="margin-top: 20px; padding: 16px 20px; background: rgba(220,38,38,0.05); border: 1px solid rgba(220,38,38,0.2); border-radius: 12px; display: flex; gap: 12px; align-items: center;">
              <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#dc2626" stroke-width="2" style="flex-shrink: 0;"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 9v3.75m-9.303 3.376c-.866 1.5.217 3.374 1.948 3.374h14.71c1.73 0 2.813-1.874 1.948-3.374L13.949 3.378c-.866-1.5-3.032-1.5-3.898 0L2.697 16.126zM12 15.75h.007v.008H12v-.008z"/></svg>
              <p style="font-size: 14px; color: var(--prism-text); line-height: 1.6; margin: 0;"><strong>Critical:</strong> Bulk device actions must be safely executable with keyboard-only flows.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider" />

          <!-- Principle 5 -->
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h3 id="accessible-tables" class="doc-h3"><span style="color: var(--prism-violet); font-weight: 700; margin-right: 4px;">5.</span> Use accessible data tables</h3>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Tables are the core of endpoint management.</p>
            <h4 style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; color: var(--prism-text-muted); margin-bottom: 12px;">Guidelines</h4>
            <ul class="doc-list">
              <li>Use semantic table structures</li>
              <li>Support row and cell navigation</li>
              <li>Announce selected row counts</li>
              <li>Clearly expose sortable headers</li>
              <li>Provide screen-reader-friendly pagination labels</li>
              <li>Ensure sticky headers preserve reading order</li>
              <li>Use explicit empty states instead of blank grids</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="do-dont-grid" style="margin-top: 24px;">
              <div class="do-card"><span class="card-label">Good</span><ul><li>"No unmanaged devices found"</li></ul></div>
              <div class="dont-card"><span class="card-label">Bad</span><ul><li>Empty table with no explanation</li></ul></div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider" />

          <!-- Principle 6 -->
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h3 id="clear-action-language" class="doc-h3"><span style="color: var(--prism-violet); font-weight: 700; margin-right: 4px;">6.</span> Write clear action language</h3>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Endpoint actions can impact thousands of devices.</p>
            <h4 style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; color: var(--prism-text-muted); margin-bottom: 12px;">Guidelines</h4>
            <ul class="doc-list">
              <li>Use direct verbs: <strong>Deploy patch</strong>, <strong>Isolate device</strong>, <strong>Restart endpoint</strong>, <strong>Retry failed install</strong></li>
              <li>Explain irreversible actions</li>
              <li>Avoid ambiguous CTA labels like: Proceed, Continue, Apply</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="do-dont-grid" style="margin-top: 24px;">
              <div class="do-card"><span class="card-label">Preferred</span><ul><li>"Deploy to 24 devices"</li><li>"Delete policy permanently"</li></ul></div>
              <div class="dont-card"><span class="card-label">Avoid</span><ul><li>"Proceed"</li><li>"Continue"</li><li>"Apply"</li></ul></div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider" />

          <!-- Principle 7 -->
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h3 id="motion-sensitivity" class="doc-h3"><span style="color: var(--prism-violet); font-weight: 700; margin-right: 4px;">7.</span> Respect motion and urgency sensitivity</h3>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Animated dashboards can overwhelm users. This is especially important in security dashboards with continuous threat streams.</p>
            <h4 style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; color: var(--prism-text-muted); margin-bottom: 12px;">Guidelines</h4>
            <ul class="doc-list">
              <li>Respect <code style="font-family: monospace; font-size: 13px; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 6px; background: rgba(37,99,235,0.06); color: var(--prism-violet);">prefers-reduced-motion</code> system settings</li>
              <li>Avoid flashing threat animations</li>
              <li>Use subtle transitions in live alert feeds</li>
              <li>Pause auto-refreshing charts when focused</li>
              <li>Let users control refresh intervals</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider" />

          <!-- Principle 8 -->
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h3 id="semantic-structure" class="doc-h3"><span style="color: var(--prism-violet); font-weight: 700; margin-right: 4px;">8.</span> Support screen readers with semantic structure</h3>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Large enterprise interfaces need strong semantic hierarchy.</p>
            <h4 style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; color: var(--prism-text-muted); margin-bottom: 12px;">Guidelines</h4>
            <ul class="doc-list">
              <li>Use landmarks: <strong>Header</strong>, <strong>Navigation</strong>, <strong>Main content</strong>, <strong>Sidebar</strong></li>
              <li>Use heading hierarchy consistently</li>
              <li>Announce live status updates via <code style="font-family: monospace; font-size: 13px; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 6px; background: rgba(37,99,235,0.06); color: var(--prism-violet);">aria-live</code> regions</li>
              <li>Use ARIA labels only when native semantics are insufficient</li>
              <li>Ensure drawer open/close state is announced</li>
            </ul>
            <div style="margin-top: 20px; padding: 16px 20px; background: rgba(220,38,38,0.05); border: 1px solid rgba(220,38,38,0.2); border-radius: 12px; display: flex; gap: 12px; align-items: center;">
              <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#dc2626" stroke-width="2" style="flex-shrink: 0;"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 9v3.75m-9.303 3.376c-.866 1.5.217 3.374 1.948 3.374h14.71c1.73 0 2.813-1.874 1.948-3.374L13.949 3.378c-.866-1.5-3.032-1.5-3.898 0L2.697 16.126zM12 15.75h.007v.008H12v-.008z"/></svg>
              <p style="font-size: 14px; color: var(--prism-text); line-height: 1.6; margin: 0;"><strong>Important:</strong> Do not use generic containers where semantic regions are expected.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider" />

          <!-- Principle 9 -->
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h3 id="test-workflows" class="doc-h3"><span style="color: var(--prism-violet); font-weight: 700; margin-right: 4px;">9.</span> Test real enterprise workflows</h3>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Accessibility validation must reflect real endpoint tasks.</p>
            <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 24px; margin-top: 24px;">
              <div style="padding: 24px; background: var(--prism-surface); border: 1px solid var(--prism-border); border-radius: 12px;">
                <h4 style="font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--prism-text); margin-bottom: 16px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px;">
                  <svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="#2563eb" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"/></svg>
                  Test critical journeys
                </h4>
                <ul class="doc-list" style="border: none; background: transparent; padding: 0;">
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Patch deployment</li>
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Remote troubleshooting</li>
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Device isolation</li>
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Compliance reporting</li>
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Policy creation</li>
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Alert triage</li>
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Bulk software uninstall</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div style="padding: 24px; background: var(--prism-surface); border: 1px solid var(--prism-border); border-radius: 12px;">
                <h4 style="font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--prism-text); margin-bottom: 16px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px;">
                  <svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="#2563eb" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M11.42 15.17l-5.384-3.19m0 0A9 9 0 1020.094 9.34M6.036 11.98l5.384 3.19m0 0l5.384-3.19"/></svg>
                  Testing methods
                </h4>
                <ul class="doc-list" style="border: none; background: transparent; padding: 0;">
